<h1>Problem 1747 - 2021 IMOSL, G4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(ABCD\) be a quadrilateral inscribed in a circle \(\Omega.\) Let the tangent to \(\Omega\) at \(D\) meet rays \(BA\) and \(BC\) at \(E\) and \(F,\) respectively. A point \(T\) is chosen inside \(\triangle ABC\) so that \(\overline{TE}\parallel\overline{CD}\) and \(\overline{TF}\parallel\overline{AD}.\) Let \(K\ne D\) be a point on segment \(DF\) satisfying \(TD=TK.\) Prove that lines \(AC,DT,\) and \(BK\) are concurrent.</p>
<h2>Idea</h2>
<p>The main idea is to again go for the <b>leap of faith</b>, but not get distracted -
within our limits, we obtain results we can prove and keep the end goal clear. Tunnel
vision should not develop <i>after</i> taking the leap.</p>
